rious%20health%20concerns%2C%20Mr%20Kejriwal%20highlighted%20the%20need%20for%20medical%20tests%2C%20including%20a%20PET-CT%20scan%2C%20following%20a%20weight%20loss%20of%207%20kg%20and%20elevated%20ketone%20levels.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Kejriwal%20was%20initially%20granted%20interim%20bail%20until%20June%201%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20to%20facilitate%20his%20participation%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20election%20campaign.%C2%A0As%20per%20the%20ruling%2C%20he%20is%20required%20to%20surrender%20and%20return%20to%20Tihar%20Jail%20on%20June%202.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMax%20Hospital's%20medical%20team%20has%20already%20conducted%20preliminary%20examinations.%20The%20Chief%20Minister's%20legal%20counsel%20argued%20that%20these%20tests%20are%20crucial%20for%20his%20well-being%20and%20requested%20the%20court%20to%20consider%20the%20extension%20to%20complete%20the%20necessary%20medical%20investigations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20interim%20bail%20granted%20to%20Mr%20Kejriwal%20has%20sparked%20controversy%2C%20with%20BJP%20leaders%20alleging%20that%20he%20received%20%26quot%3Bspecial%20treatment%26quot%3B%20from%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%20However%2C%20the%20justices%20involved%20in%20granting%20the%20bail%20have%20firmly%20stated%20that%20no%20exceptions%20were%20made%20in%20Mr%20Kejriwal's%20favour.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ongoing%20probe%20revolves%20around%20alleged%20irregularities%20in%20the%20formulation%20and%20implementation%20of%20the%20Delhi%20excise%20policy%20(2021-22).%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20excise%20policy%2C%20introduced%20to%20bring%20an%20overhaul%20to%20the%20national%20capital's%20liquor%20business%2C%20promised%20a%20more%20modern%20shopping%20experience%20with%20discounts%20and%20offers.%20However%2C%20Delhi%20Lieutenant%20Governor%20Vinai%20Kumar%20Saxena's%20order%20to%20investigate%20alleged%20irregularities%20prompted%20the%20policy's%20cancellation.%20The%20AAP%20accuses%20Mr%20Saxena's%20predecessor%2C%20Anil%20Baijal%2C%20of%20making%20last-minute%20changes%20that%20adversely%20affected%20the%20policy's%20revenue%20expectations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAAP%20leader%20and%20former%20deputy%20chief%20minister%20of%20Delhi%20Manish%20Sisodia%20is%20already%20under%20judicial%20custody%20in%20connection%20with%20the%20case.%20Mr%20Sisodia%2C%20the%20former%20Delhi%20Deputy%20Chief%20Minister%2C%20was%20arrested%20by%20the%20Central%20Bureau%20of%20Investigation%20(CBI)%20on%20February%2026%20last%20year%2C%20while%20party%20leader%20Sanjay%20Singh%2C%20a%20Rajya%20Sabha%20member%2C%20was%20arrested%20by%20the%20ED%20on%20October%205%20and%20was%20granted%20bail%20in%20April%20this%20year.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1716784200000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-05%2F4i6uabig_arvind-kejriwal_625x300_12_May_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Farvind-kejriwal-requests-supreme-court-to-extend-interim-bail-by-7-days-5753785%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Delhi%20Chief%20Minister%20Arvind%20Kejriwal%20has%20petitioned%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20for%20a%20seven-day%20extension%20on%20his%20interim%20bail%20in%20connection%20with%20the%20Delhi%20liquor%20policy%20case.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Farvind-kejriwal-requests-supreme-court-to-extend-interim-bail-by-7-days-5753785%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Farvind-kejriwal-requests-supreme-court-to-extend-interim-bail-by-7-days-5753785%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Farvind-kejriwal-requests-supreme-court-to-extend-interim-bail-by-7-days-5753785%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22China%20Box%20Office%3A%20%E2%80%98The%20Last%20Frenzy%E2%80%99%20Keeps%20Theatrical%20Lead%20as%20Momentum%20Slows%20Further%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1716783952000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F05%2FThe-Last-Frenzy-3x2cr-res.jpg%3Fw%3D1000%26h%3D563%26crop%3D1%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F%3Fp%3D1236016976%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%E2%80%9CThe%20Last%20Frenzy%2C%E2%80%9D%20a%20comedy%20film%20about%20a%20dying%20man%E2%80%99s%20last%20hurrah%2C%20retained%20the%20top%20spot%20in%20mainland%20Chinese%20cinemas%20for%20the%20third%20weekend%20of%20its%20four%20weeks%20on%20release.%20Other%20signs%20of%20theatrical%20malaise%20were%20plentiful.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20Last%20Frenzy%E2%80%9D%20earned%20%245.8%20million%20(RMB41.5%20million)%20between%20Friday%20and%20Sunday%2C%20according%20to%20data%20from%20consultancy%20firm%20%5B%E2%80%A6%5D%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Patrick%20Frater%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F2024%2Ffilm%2Fnews%2Fchina-box-office-weekend-last-frenzy-1236016976%2F%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fvariety.com%2F2024%2Ffilm%2Fnews%2Fchina-box-office-weekend-last-frenzy-1236016976%2Famp%2F%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F2024%2Ffilm%2Fnews%2Fchina-box-office-weekend-last-frenzy-1236016976%2Famp%2F%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Indian%20Judge%20Who%20Voted%20In%20Favour%20Of%20World%20Court's%20Order%20Against%20Israel%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20International%20Court%20of%20Justice%20(ICJ)%20on%20Friday%20ordered%20Israel%20to%20immediately%20halt%20its%20military%20operations%20in%20Rafah%2C%20and%20one%20of%20the%20judges%20who%20favoured%20the%20ruling%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.icj-cij.org%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2F2023-04%2F20230413_Bhandari_en.pdf%5C%22%3EJudge%20Dalveer%20Bhandari%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20Indian%20representative%20at%20the%20ICJ.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Bhandari%2C%20an%20esteemed%20jurist%20with%20a%20distinguished%20career%2C%20has%20been%20a%20member%20of%20the%20ICJ%20since%202012.%20Born%20in%20Rajasthan's%20Jodhpur%20in%201947%2C%20he%20has%20received%20numerous%20accolades%2C%20including%20the%20Padma%20Bhushan%20in%202014.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Bhandari%20has%20advocated%20numerous%20landmark%20cases%20at%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%20He%20served%20as%20a%20senior%20judge%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20having%20been%20elevated%20to%20the%20position%20on%2028%20October%2C%202005.%20He%20delivered%20numerous%20judgments%20in%20areas%20including%20public%20interest%20litigation%2C%20constitutional%20law%2C%20criminal%20law%2C%20civil%20procedure%2C%20administrative%20law%2C%20arbitration%2C%20family%20law%2C%20labour%20and%20industrial%20law%2C%20and%20corporate%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%202012%2C%20Mr%20Bhandari%20has%20been%20associated%20with%20all%20cases%20decided%20by%20the%20ICJ%2C%20contributing%20to%20significant%20issues%20such%20as%20maritime%20disputes%2C%20whaling%20in%20Antarctica%2C%20genocide%2C%20continental%20shelf%20delimitation%2C%20nuclear%20disarmament%2C%20terrorism%20financing%2C%20and%20sovereign%20rights%20violation%2C%20among%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJudge%20Bhandari%20chaired%20the%20Delhi%20Centre%20of%20the%20International%20Law%20Association%20for%20several%20years.%20Prior%20to%20his%20appointment%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20he%20was%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20the%20Bombay%20High%20Court.%20His%20notable%20ruling%20in%20a%20divorce%20case%20established%20that%20an%20irretrievable%20breakdown%20of%20marriage%20could%20be%20grounds%20for%20divorce%2C%20prompting%20the%20Centre%20to%20seriously%20consider%20amending%20the%20Hindu%20Marriage%20Act%2C%201955.%20He%20has%20been%20honoured%20as%20one%20of%20the%2015%20most%20esteemed%20and%20distinguished%20alumni%20in%20the%20150-year%20history%20of%20Northwestern%20University%20School%20of%20Law%20in%20Chicago%2C%20where%20he%20earned%20his%20Master%20of%20Law%20in%201971.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ICJ%20ruling%2C%20announced%20by%20Presiding%20Judge%20Nawaf%20Salam%2C%20came%20in%20response%20to%20an%20application%20from%20South%20Africa%20accusing%20Israel%20of%20actions%20amounting%20to%20genocide.%20The%20ruling%20mandates%20that%20Israel%20must%20cease%20any%20actions%20that%20could%20lead%20to%20the%20physical%20destruction%20of%20the%20Palestinian%20population%20in%20Rafah.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court's%20decision%20was%20supported%20by%20a%2013-2%20vote%2C%20with%20only%20Judges%20Julia%20Sebutinde%20from%20Uganda%20and%20former%20Israeli%20High%20Court%20President%20Judge%20Aharon%20Barak%20dissenting.%20The%20ruling%20also%20stressed%20the%20need%20for%20Israel%20to%20provide%20unhindered%20humanitarian%20aid%20and%20access%20to%20UN%20bodies%20investigating%20the%20allegations%20of%20genocide.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20ICJ's%20ruling%2C%20Israel%20has%20firmly%20rejected%20the%20order.%20Israel's%20National%20Security%20Adviser%20Tzachi%20Hanegbi%2C%20alongside%20the%20foreign%20ministry%2C%20stated%20that%20Israel's%20military%20operations%20in%20Rafah%20are%20in%20accordance%20with%20international%20law%20and%20that%20they%20have%20no%20intention%20of%20creating%20conditions%20that%20would%20lead%20to%20the%20destruction%20of%20the%20Palestinian%20population.%20Israel's%20War%20cabinet%20minister%20Benny%20Gantz%20echoed%20this%20sentiment%2C%20asserting%20that%20military%20operations%20would%20continue%20wherever%20deemed%20necessary.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPalestinian%20Ambassador%20to%20the%20UN%2C%20Riyad%20Mansour%2C%20praised%20the%20ruling%2C%20urging%20for%20its%20immediate%20implementation.%20He%20stressed%20that%20adherence%20to%20ICJ%20resolutions%20is%20mandatory%2C%20highlighting%20Israel's%20obligation%20as%20a%20party%20to%20the%20Genocide%20Convention.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1716783540000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-05%2F1nmql4v_judge-dalveer-bhandari-_625x300_27_May_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-new